			<div class="content" id="post-content-2319340">
									

<p>I'm no-voting. I think it's a good effort, but not quite enough to get me to really laugh, especially because the containment procedures were a little oddly worded/thought-out.</p>
<p>Mostly this line:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>are currently attempting to generate a counter-meme: that SCP-005-J-EX is &quot;really annoying&quot; and should be suppressed.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Like&#8230; I'm not 100% sure how that's a counter-meme, or at least the wording using a colon there is odd. Granted, we're also talking about the difference between the meme-in-real-world terms versus the meme-in-Foundation-universe terms, such that when I see &quot;counter-meme&quot; I'm expecting something involving a jpeg that blows your head off.</p>
<p>I mean, the procedures don't have to be 100% credible given the joke, but still.</p>

